On one of the Sabbath days, Jesus was walking through the grainfields with his disciples. And the disciples began to pluck the heads of grain.
The Pharisees said to Jesus, "Look! It is not lawful to do this work on the Sabbath. Why do your disciples do it?"
He answered, "Have you never read what David did? He and his men were hungry. They needed food.
It was at the time when Abiathar was high priest. David entered the house of God and ate the showbread, which was lawful only for the priests to eat. And he also gave some to his men.
Then Jesus said to them, "The Sabbath was made for man, not man for the Sabbath."
Therefore the Son of Man is Lord even of the Sabbath.
Healing on Saturday
One Sabbath Jesus entered the synagogue, and a man with a shriveled hand was there.
Some of the Pharisees were trying to find fault with Jesus. They were watching him closely. They wanted to see if he would heal the man on the Sabbath.
Jesus spoke to the man with the withered hand. He said to him, "Stand up in front of everyone."
Then Jesus asked them, "What does the law say about what should be done on the Sabbath? Does it command good or evil? Does it save life or destroy it?" But no one answered.
Jesus looked around in anger. He was very angry because their hearts were hardened. Then he said to the man, "Stretch out your hand." And he stretched it out, and his hand was restored.
Then the Pharisees went and began to plot with the Herodians against Jesus, wanting to kill him. The crowds followed Jesus.
Jesus went to the Sea of Galilee with his disciples, and a large crowd from Galilee followed him.
The people heard about all that Jesus was doing. Large crowds came to him from Judea, Jerusalem, Idumea, beyond the Jordan River, and from the region around Tyre and Sidon.
Jesus ordered his disciples, because of the crowd, to prepare a small boat for him. This would prevent people from crowding around him.
Jesus healed many people. Therefore, the sick were jostling to touch him.
When the people who had evil spirits saw him, they fell down before him. The spirits cried out, "You are the Son of God!"
